Title: Letting Go
---
I don't like the dark.
I'd rather be clothed
than naked.

Yet You tell me
I must let go of all that
clothes me --

my joys and fears,
my worries and even
my imaginings --

and give myself
to the dark emptiness
where You wait

to be born in me.
